aa(lp55
VNow, race is one of those topics in America
p56
aVthat makes people extraordinarily uncomfortable.
p57
aVYou bring it up at a dinner party
p58
aVor in a workplace environment,
p59
aVit is literally the conversational equivalent
p60
aVof touching the third rail.
p61
aVThere is shock,
p62
aVfollowed by a long silence.
p63
aVAnd even coming here today,
p64
aVI told some friends and colleagues
p65
aVthat I planned to talk about race,
p66
aVand they warned me, they told me, don't do it,
p67
aVthat there'd be huge risks
p68
aVin me talking about this topic,
p69
aVthat people might think I'm a militant black woman
p70
aVand I would ruin my career.
p71
aVAnd I have to tell you,
p72
aVI actually for a moment was a bit afraid.
p73
aVThen I realized,
p74
aVthe first step to solving any problem
p75
aVis to not hide from it,
p76
aVand the first step to any form of action
p77
aVis awareness.
